        "body": "The Orbcomm team has had some opportunities to write interesting code around JPA and Beans. It is worth jotting down some of the high level comments, as it could help others if they want to do something with those patterns.\n\nFor example:\n- Multiple DataSources (Primary and Seconday Databases)\n- Multiple Beans around EntityManagers, TransactionManagers, etc.\n- Leveraging entityManager with createQuery() and createNativeQuery() - leveraging JPQL and SQL\n\n# Dependency Structure Overview\n```java\nclient-common-core\n|__ SpringDataJpaReadingConfiguration.java (defines Beans: DataSourceProperties, HikariProperties, HikariDataSource, EntityManagerFactory, PlatformTransactionManager)\n|__ ReadRepositoryConfig.java (links to entityManagerFactor, transactionManager)\n|__ ...\n\nclient-consumer-base\n|__ SpringDataJpaReadingConfigurationTest.java\n```\n\n# Example Test Using Beans defined elsewhere\n\nSpringDataJpaReadingConfigurationTest in client-consumer-base looks like:\n\n```java\n@SpringBootTest(classes = {\n        SpringDataJpaReadingConfiguration.class,\n        ReadRepositoryConfig.class,\n})\npublic class SpringDataJpaReadingConfigurationTest {\n\n    @Autowired\n    @Qualifier(\"readingDataSourceProperties\")\n    private DataSourceProperties dataSourceProperties;\n\n    @DisplayName(\"Slave DataSource Properties Loaded\")\n    @Test\n    void whenContextIsLoaded_ThenSlaveDataSourcePropertiesExist() {\n        assertNotNull(dataSourceProperties);\n        assertNotNull(dataSourceProperties.getUrl());\n        assertNotNull(dataSourceProperties.getUsername());\n        assertNotNull(dataSourceProperties.getPassword());\n    }\n\n    ...\n\n}\n```",
